	<!-- TEXT  -->
	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>Making A Mesa Things</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_HELP">
			<Text>It is a delegation from the mining company again, Your Gloriousness. I am not sure what they are after, but I imagine it is along the lines of more money.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>The Natural Wonder permenantly yields +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production, [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism and [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Points.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>The Natural Wonder permenantly yields +4 [ICON_FOOD] Food.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Though the locals must give up {2_InstantYield}, the City receives a free Stone Works, which additionally yields +2 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture and +2 [ICON_GOLD] Gold.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>The local Hotel yields +10 [ICON_GOLD] Gold and +10 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism. However, the Natural Wonder loses up to -10 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>*The company want a pay rise, as expected.*[NEWLINE]Thankfully these muppets don't understand inflation: we're not actually paying them anything extra in real terms.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*The miners are complaining about the damp conditions, which persist in spite of all efforts to rectify them.*[NEWLINE]I think they may have actually stumbled upon something really important here: the rocks that make up the Mesa are extremely good at draining water... perhaps we ought to try farming the surrounding area.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*The labourers demand consignments of dynamite to accelerate the mining process.*[NEWLINE]While this may required some oversight, the quantities of stone we could have access to are immense!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MESA_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The labourers are unhappy with the recent attempts of the ski industry to build a resort ontop of their mining town*[NEWLINE]I've been looking at this brochure, and apparently, when the sun hits that ridge just right, those hills sing.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
